                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra (name of St Mary in Texts I-4, I-5);
                           titles and numbers of the Pss. and Canticles; incipits and numbers of
                           Songs; title of Texts I-2, I-3 and I-5; name and traditional
                           interpretation of the Hebrew letters in Ps. 118; initial word and
                           abbreviation of refrains of Texts I-4 and I-5; elements of the
                           punctuation signs and text dividers; Ethiopic numerals or their
                           elements.
 
 A few groups of lines (alternating with black lines)
                           on the incipit page of Text I-1; two lines (alternating with black lines)
                           on the incipit page of Texts I-3, I-4 and I-5.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#3r">3r</locus> (incipit of Text I-1): elaborate, uncoloured
                        ornamental band; anthropomorphic and geometric motifs.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#154ra">f. 154ra</locus>
                           <desc>: Calendaric note. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#154ra">154ra</locus>: በዘተአምር፡ መፍቅደ፡ ጾም፡ ዘ፲ወ፪፡
                              አውራኅ...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note lists the months and an estimated length of the days,
                              measured in ጫማ “feet”, for each of them. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#154rb">f. 154rb</locus>
                           <desc>: Traditional genealogy.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#154rb">154rb</locus>: ትውልድ፡ ሥልጣን፡ በአት፡ ወልዶ፡ ለተወለደ፡
                              መድኅን፡ ወተወልደ፡ መድኅን... </quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note starts with a certain Śǝlṭan or Bäʾat and ends with Walda
                              Māryām. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The Psalms are divided into groups of ten separated by
                           means of a chain of red and black dots.
 - The scribe reduced the
                           size of his handwriting to accommodate the end of the line: e.g., <locus target="#10r">10r</locus>, 27r, 44r, 111v, 128r, 141v.
 - Part of
                           the line is taken up: <locus target="#74v">74v</locus>, 87r, 104r, 107r,
                           109r, 109v, 126v, 134r, 140v, 141r, 143r.
 - Part of the line is
                           taken down: <locus target="#85r">85r</locus>, 103v, 105r, 105v, 106v,
                           107r, 145r.
 - Some omissions and corrections are written
                           interlineally or as a continuation of the preceding verse: e.g., <locus target="#4v">4v</locus>, 9v, 11v, 23v, 27v, 35r, 54r, 62v, 110v.
                           - Corrections written over erased words and passages: e.g., <locus target="#12r">12r</locus>, 28r, 69v, 123v, 130v.
 - Erasures:
                           e.g., <locus target="#25v">25v</locus>, 35r, 53v, 77v, 130r.
 - Two
                           lines are left unfilled on <locus target="#46r">46r</locus>. 
 - A
                           female name has been erased from the supplication formula: <locus target="#38r">38r</locus>. 
 - Two notes of several lines have
                           been erased: <locus target="#154ra">154ra</locus>.
 - Scribbles,
                           writing exercises (also in the Ethiopic syllabary): <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>, 153v, inner sides of both boards.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">A red thread is inserted in the right upper corner
                              of <locus target="#111">fol. 111</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
